<subSubSection id="38BE6558FF8BFF97FF73F873A26E51AF" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="416" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="701B36D3FF8BFF97FF73F873A3F25183" blockId="14.[151,1437,1798,2003]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,1328]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="416" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8BFF96FF73F873A72856F8" bold="true" box="[199,321,1942,1967]" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8BFF96FEFCF872A7DF56F9" authorityName="Kaila &amp; Nupponen" authorityYear="2018" box="[328,438,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perona">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8BFF96FEFCF872A7DF56F9" box="[328,438,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">E. perona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small, chalky white species with brown plical and discal spots on the forewing. It is close to 
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8BFF96FF41F85EA7FA5685" authorityName="Parenti. Left" authorityYear="1981" box="[245,403,1978,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8BFF96FF41F85EA7FA5685" box="[245,403,1978,2002]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="415">E. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Their distinctive difference is in the shape of the juxta lobes which are basally convex and distally more or less concave in 
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FDADFF7CA4D251E7" authorityName="Parenti. Left" authorityYear="1981" box="[537,699,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FDADFF7CA4D251E7" box="[537,699,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">E. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, evenly convex in 
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FC14FF7CA27351E7" box="[928,1050,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FC14FF7CA27F51E7" authorityName="Kaila &amp; Nupponen" authorityYear="2018" box="[928,1046,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perona">E. perona</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Furthermore, the juxta lobes are markedly prolonged in 
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FE29FF58A4535183" authorityName="Parenti. Left" authorityYear="1981" box="[413,570,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bimaculata">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FE29FF58A4535183" box="[413,570,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">E. bimaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not so in 
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FD1BFF58A54C5183" box="[687,805,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FD1BFF58A5495183" authorityName="Kaila &amp; Nupponen" authorityYear="2018" box="[687,800,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perona">E. perona</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
This trait also distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FBD1FF58A2BB5183" authorityName="Kaila &amp; Nupponen" authorityYear="2018" box="[1125,1234,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perona">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FBD1FF58A2BB5183" box="[1125,1234,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">E. perona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FAA3FF58A3F25183" box="[1303,1435,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<taxonomicName id="B7A44D50FF8AFF97FAA3FF58A3FE5183" box="[1303,1431,189,212]" class="Insecta" family="Elachistidae" genus="Elachista" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semnani">E. semnani</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="701B36D3FF8AFF97FF73FF3AA26E51AF" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1328]" box="[199,1031,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FF73FF3AA47D51AF" bold="true" box="[199,532,223,248]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Molecular characterization.</emphasis>
No material was available for genetic study.
