</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="38BE6558FF8AFF97FF73FB2AA7B7545A" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="701B36D3FF8AFF97FF73FB2AA7B7545A" blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1328]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FF73FB2AA72755BF" bold="true" box="[199,334,1231,1256]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is derived from the Greek word 
<emphasis id="42D0EAC1FF8AFF97FC87FB34A5E955BF" box="[819,896,1233,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">perone</emphasis>
, a pointed item aimed at piercing. This refers to the acute apex of the phallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
